latestPosts.caption:
In times of conflict, choices speak louder than campaigns.

At @virgio.official, we’re proud to say—we’re built, designed, and delivered entirely from India.
From our designers and manufacturers to the technology that powers us—this is a truly homegrown movement.

We consciously choose not to build from regions that stand against our values or ally with those who do.
Because fashion is not just about trends. It’s about standing for something.

Proud to be Indian. Committed to creating from India.
For a world that deserves fashion with a spine.

#MakeInIndia #BuiltFromIndia #VIRGIO #IndiaFirst #AtmanirbharBharat #FashionWithPurpose

latestPosts.caption:
The future of fashion isn’t just about great design—it’s about speed, sustainability, and supply chain mastery.

At @india_fashion_forum 2025, we discussed how fashion today is split between two extremes:

Fast fashion, which has perfected demand-driven supply chains but at a massive environmental cost.
Sustainable fashion, which has brought in innovation but struggles to scale efficiently.

The real opportunity? Bringing the best of both worlds together.

The next generation of fashion brands won’t just be design houses—they’ll be supply chain powerhouses, built to create in real time, without waste.

At @virgio.official , we’re already building that future. What’s your take?

latestPosts.caption:
#diwali2024 marks an eventful year for us at @virgio.official. We overcame so many non believers and obstacles in making ‘good’ fashion. We couldn’t have done it without our #virgiocircle holding our hand in every step of this journey. 

So this Diwali, we have started a VIRGIO  #GiveBack Initiative - “Smile in Style”, with the only intent of spreading smiles beyond our consumer base.  So this Diwali, let’s spread joy and light up the lives of underprivileged children. We recently came across a recent study where it is mentioned that millions of children in India celebrate Diwali with out new clothes.

Imagine the joy and excitement on their faces when they receive a brand new, sustainable outfit. Your support has given us confidence in our journey so far. So we took the liberty in setting us a goal of dressing up 10,000 kids with new outfits. Your purchase will not only bring happiness to a child but also support a more sustainable world. Let’s create a brighter future together.

PS: we are not manufacturing new outfits but our team is busy scouting for unsold inventory in kids wear across the country. Anyone who is struggling with unsold inventory in kids wear please reach out to us
